Guaranteeing that the company can obtain an extension of credit regardless
of the consumer's previous credit history - unless the statement discloses the
eligibility requirements for obtaining a credit extension. (2) Guaranteeing
the deletion of adverse credit history unless it is inaccurate or obsolete. (3)
Promising specific points increase in the consumer's credit scores.
4. Make or advise a consumer to provide untrue or misleading statements to
any consumer credit reporting agency, lenders, or any entity involved in
extending credit to the consumer.
5. Remove accurate information from the consumer's credit record.
6. Make or encourage a consumer to create a new credit record using a
different name, address, SS number, or employment number.
7. Perform credit repair services without a written contract signed by and given
to the consumer, which should include the following: (1) Full and detailed
description of the services to be performed. (2) Expected costs and payment
terms. (3) And copies of the "Consumer Credit File Rights Under State and
Federal Law" and the "Notice of Cancellation".
8. Perform credit repair services without giving the consumer the signed
contract and other documents.
9. Provide services before the end of the 3-business-day period that allows the
consumer to cancel the contract.
10.Provide credit repair services without informing clients about their rights
under state and federal law, including the consumer's right to cancel within
three business days after signing.
11.Submit a consumer's credit dispute to any consumer credit reporting agency
without their knowledge.
12.Provide credit repair services without license or registration in the state
where it operates.
13.Transfer the credit repair business certificate of registration to a different
name or business name without approval from the regulatory authority or
licensing body that issued the certificate.
14.Exceed six months from the date the buyer signed the contract of agreement
to complete the agreed services.
Section 1679c: Disclosures
Any credit repair organization shall provide any consumer with the following
written statement before any contract or agreement between the consumer and the
credit repair organization is executed:

