The Fair Credit Reporting Act (FCRA) offers various provisions to help prevent
identity theft and fraud. Here's a list of identity theft prevention measures, fraud
alerts, and active-duty alerts by the FCRA.
(a) On Call Fraud Alerts:
(1) Initial fraud Alerts
If a consumer, or their representative, suspects fraud or identity theft and requests a
fraud alert, the consumer reporting agency must:
• Add a fraud alert to the consumer's file for at least 1 year unless the
consumer requests its removal earlier.
• Share the fraud alert with other consumer reporting agencies.
(2) Access to Free Reports
When a fraud alert is added, the consumer reporting agency must:
• Inform the consumer that they can request a free copy of their file.

57
