If a consumer contacts a consumer reporting agency that does not have nationwide
files to report suspected fraud or related crime, including identity theft, the agency
must inform the consumer on how to contact the Bureau and a nationwide
consumer reporting agency for more detailed information and to request alerts.
(h) Limitations on Use of Information for Credit Extensions
(1) Requirements for Initial and Active-Duty Alerts
(A) Notification: Each initial fraud alert and active-duty alert must inform
potential users of the consumer report that the consumer does not authorize the
following:
• New credit plans or extensions of credit, other than under an open-end
credit plan, in the name of the consumer

