• Issuance of additional cards on existing accounts requested by the
consumer.
• Increase in credit limits on existing accounts.
Except in accordance with "Limitation on Users".
(B) Limitation on Users:
(i) General Rule: No new credit plans, extensions of credit, additional
cards, or credit limit increases can be authorized unless the user
utilizes reasonable policies and procedures to form a reasonable belief
that the user knows the identity of the person making the request.
(ii) Verification: If the consumer has provided a telephone number for
identity verification, the user must contact the consumer at that
number or take reasonable steps to confirm the consumer's identity
and ensure the request is not due to identity theft before authorizing
any new credit.
(2) Requirements for Extended Alerts
(A) Notification: Each extended alert shall include information that
provides all prospective users of a consumer report relating to a
consumer with:
(i) Notification that the consumer does not authorize any new credit
plan or extension of credit, except for an open-end credit plan, or
any additional card or increase in credit limit on an existing
account unless verified following the Limitation on Users.
(ii) A telephone number or other reasonable contact method
designated by the consumer.
(B) Limitation on users: No prospective user of a consumer report or credit
score that includes an extended fraud alert may establish a new credit
plan, extend credit, issue an additional card, or increase the credit limit
on an existing account, unless they contact the consumer in person or
using the specified contact method to confirm the request is not due to
identity theft.
