(1) Definition:
For purposes of this subsection, the following terms mean:
Consumer reporting agency - an agency that compiles and maintains nationwide
consumer files and regularly assembles, evaluates, and maintains information for
furnishing consumer reports to third parties bearing on a consumer's
creditworthiness, credit standing, or credit capacity. This includes:
Public record information.
Credit account information from businesses that provide this information regularly.
Proper identification - A consumer reporting agency shall require, as a condition of
making the disclosures required under section 609 (Disclosures to Consumers),
that the consumer furnish proper identification.
Security freeze' - a restriction that prohibits a consumer reporting agency from
disclosing the contents of a consumer report that is subject to such security freeze
to any person requesting the consumer report.
(2) Placement of security freeze
(A) General Rule: Upon receiving a direct request from a consumer that a
consumer reporting agency place a security freeze, and upon receiving proper
identification from the consumer, the consumer reporting agency shall, free of
charge, place the security freeze not later than:
• For requests made by toll-free phone or secure electronic means, within 1
business day of receiving the request from the consumer.
• For requests made by mail, within 3 business days of receiving the request
from the consumer.
(B) Confirmation and additional information: Not later than 5 business days
after placing a security freeze, a consumer reporting agency must:
• Send confirmation of the freeze to the consumer.
• Inform the consumer about: (1) How to remove the security freeze,
including an authentication method. And (2) their right to prevent their

