Material
(i) Certification of accuracy of information: If any information is deleted
from a consumer’s file, the information may not be reinserted in the file by
the consumer reporting agency unless the person who furnishes the
information certifies that the information is complete and accurate.
(ii) Notice to consumer: If any information that has been deleted from a
consumer’s file is reinserted in the file, the consumer reporting agency shall
notify the consumer of the reinsertion in writing not later than 5 business
days after the reinsertion or, if authorized by the consumer for that purpose,
by any other means available to the agency.
