Despite section 604 [Permissible Purposes of Consumer Reports] or any other part
of this subchapter, a court can issue an ex parte order (without notifying the other
party) to a consumer reporting agency to provide a consumer report to the FBI if:
• The request is in writing by the FBI Director or a designee not lower than a
Deputy Assistant Director or a Special Agent in Charge of a Bureau field
office.
• The request specifically identifies a consumer or account.
• The court is shown in a private session (in camera) that the report is needed
for an authorized investigation related to international terrorism or
clandestine intelligence activities.
• The investigation of a U.S. person is not solely based on First Amendment-
protected activities.
The order must not reveal that it is for a counterintelligence investigation.
