Section 1606: Determination of Annual Percentage
Rate (APR)
(a) "Annual Percentage Rate" Defined
The annual percentage rate applicable to any extension of consumer credit shall be
determined, in accordance with the regulations of the Bureau:
(1) in the case of any extension of credit other than under an open end credit plan,
as:
(A) that nominal annual percentage rate which will yield a sum equal to the
amount of the finance charge when it is applied to the unpaid balances of the
amount financed, calculated according to the actuarial method of allocating
payments made on a debt between the amount financed and the amount of
the finance charge, pursuant to which a payment is applied first to the

193
TRUTH IN LENDING ACT (TILA) - A.K.A. CONSUMER CREDIT COST DISCLOSURE
