(b) State Credit Charge Statutes
Except for what's in section 1639 [Requirements for Certain Mortgages], this
subchapter doesn't change or cancel any state laws about what types of charges,
amounts, rates, or other fees are allowed when giving or using credit. It also doesn't
make state laws apply to people or transactions they wouldn't normally apply to.
Section 1639 doesn't change how state laws apply or let anyone ignore state laws
about mortgage requirements, except where state laws conflict with requirements
for certain mortgages, and only to the extent of that conflict.
(c) Disclosure as Evidence
In any action or proceeding in any court involving a consumer credit sale, the
disclosure of the annual percentage rate as required under this subchapter in
connection with that sale may not be received as evidence that the sale was a loan
or any type of transaction other than a credit sale.
