Section 1631: Disclosure Requirements
(a) Duty of Creditor or Lessor Respecting One or More Than One
Obligor
A creditor or lessor shall disclose the information required under this subchapter to
the person obligated on a consumer lease or a consumer credit transaction. In a
transaction involving more than one obligor, a creditor or lessor, except in a
transaction under Right of Rescission as to Certain Transactions [section 1635 of
this title], need not disclose to more than one of such obligors if the obligor given
disclosure is a primary obligor.
(b) Creditor or Lessor Required to Make Disclosure
