make the disclosures. If a transaction involves more than one creditor or lessor,
only one creditor or lessor shall be required to make the disclosures. The Bureau
shall specify which creditor or lessor shall make the disclosures by regulation.
(c) Estimates as Satisfying Statutory Requirements; Basis of
Disclosure for Per Diem Interest
The Bureau may allow regulations stating that some information required by this
subchapter can be estimated when exact information is unavailable. For consumer
credit transactions where interest is calculated daily and collected at closing,
disclosures about this interest are considered accurate under this subchapter if they
are based on information known to the creditor when preparing the transaction
documents for closing.

