the appropriate forms for rescinding the transaction, as per Bureau regulations.
(b) Return of Money or Property Following Rescission
When a borrower rescinds the transaction, they are not liable for any finance or
other charges, and any security interest becomes void. The creditor must return any
money or property given by the borrower within 20 days of receiving the rescission
notice and take steps to terminate any security interest. If the creditor provided any
property, the borrower may keep it until the creditor fulfills its obligations. The
borrower must then return the property or its reasonable value if a direct return is
impractical. If the creditor does not collect the property within 20 days after the
borrower offers it, the borrower keeps the property without payment. These
procedures apply unless a court orders otherwise.
