For a credit card account, an over-the-limit fee can be charged once per billing
cycle if the credit limit is exceeded. In the following two billing cycles, such a fee
may be imposed again only if the consumer extends credit beyond the limit again
or fails to reduce the balance below the limit by the end of the billing cycle.
