(1) General Rule
The payment due date for a credit card account under an open end consumer credit
plan shall be the same day each month.
(2) Weekend or holiday due dates
If the payment due date for a credit card account under an open end consumer
credit plan is a day on which the creditor does not receive or accept payments by
mail (including weekends and holidays), the creditor may not treat a payment
received on the next business day as late for any purpose.
(p) Parental Approval Required to Increase Credit Lines for
Accounts for Which Parent Is Jointly Liable
No credit limit increase is allowed on a credit card account where a parent, legal
guardian, spouse, or another individual has assumed joint liability for debts
incurred by the consumer before they turn 21, without written approval and joint
liability assumption from that person.
(r) College Card Agreements
(1) Definitions
For purposes of this subsection, the following definitions shall apply:
(A) College affinity card — a credit card issued by a credit card issuer under an
open-end consumer credit plan in conjunction with an agreement between the
issuer and an institution of higher education, or an alumni organization or
foundation affiliated with or related to such institution, under which such cards are

