the borrower, then the required disclosures can be made anytime before the first
payment is due.
(d) Timing of Disclosure in Cases of An Addition of a Deferred
Payment Price to An Existing Outstanding Balance
If a consumer credit sale is part of a series of transactions under an agreement that
adds the deferred payment price to an existing balance, and the consumer has
approved in writing both the annual percentage rate and the method for calculating
finance charges, and the creditor has no security interest in property for which they
have received payments totaling the sales price plus any finance charges, then the
required disclosures can be made anytime before the first payment for that sale is

