Section 1639: Requirements for Certain Mortgages
(a) Disclosures
(1) Specific disclosures
For certain high-cost mortgages, the creditor must clearly disclose the following in
conspicuous type size:
(A) "You are not required to complete this agreement merely because you
have received these disclosures or have signed a loan application.".
(B) "If you obtain this loan, the lender will have a mortgage on your home.
You could lose your home, and any money you have put into it, if you do not
meet your obligations under the loan.".
(2) Annual percentage rate
In addition to the required disclosures, the creditor must also provide:
(A) For a fixed-rate loan: the annual percentage rate (APR) and the regular
monthly payment amount.
(B) For any other type of loan: the APR, the regular monthly payment
amount, a note that the interest rate and monthly payment may increase, and
the maximum monthly payment amount based on the highest allowed
interest rate.
(b) Time of Disclosures
(1) General Rule

