With respect to loans made, guaranteed, or insured by Federal departments or
agencies identified in subsection (b)(3)(B)(ii), such departments or agencies may
exempt refinancings under a streamlined refinancing from this income verification
requirement as long as the following conditions are met:
(A) The consumer is not 30 days or more past due on the prior existing
residential mortgage loan.
(B) The refinancing does not increase the principal balance outstanding on
the prior existing residential mortgage loan, except to the extent of fees and
charges allowed by the department or agency making, guaranteeing, or
insuring the refinancing.
(C) Total points and fees other than bona fide third-party charges not
retained by the mortgage originator, creditor, or an affiliate of the creditor or

