Anyone who knowingly receives, hides, uses, or transports money, goods, services,
or anything of value (except tickets for interstate or foreign transportation) that (1)
totals $1,000 or more within a year, (2) has been involved in interstate or
international commerce, and (3) was obtained with a counterfeit, fake, altered,
forged, lost, stolen, or fraudulently obtained credit card.
(e) Receipt, Concealment, Etc., Of Tickets for Interstate or Foreign
Transportation Obtained by Use of Card
Anyone who knowingly receives, hides, uses, sells, or transports in interstate or
international commerce one or more transportation tickets that (1) total $500 or
more within a year, and (2) were bought or obtained with counterfeit, fake, altered,
forged, lost, stolen, or fraudulently obtained credit cards.
(f) Furnishing of Money, Etc., Through Use of Card
Anyone who knowingly provides money, property, services, or anything of value
totaling $1,000 or more in a year using a counterfeit, fake, altered, forged, lost,
stolen, or fraudulently obtained credit card in a transaction involving interstate or
foreign commerce can be fined up to $10,000, imprisoned for up to ten years, or
both.
