THE COMPLETE GUIDE TO CREDIT LAWS
In issuing rules required by this subsection, the Bureau may establish different
standards for different types of fees and charges, as appropriate.
(e) Safe Harbor Rule Authorized
The Bureau, in consultation with the Comptroller of the Currency, the Federal
Deposit Insurance Corporation Board, the Director of the Office of Thrift
Supervision, and the National Credit Union Administration Board, can create rules
that establish a standard amount for any penalty fee or charge mentioned in
subsection (a). This standard amount will be considered reasonable and
proportional to the specific issue or violation it addresses.
Section 1665e. Consideration of Ability to Repay
A card issuer may not open any credit card account for any consumer under an
open-end consumer credit plan, or increase any credit limit applicable to such
account, unless the card issuer considers the ability of the consumer to make the
required payments under the terms of such account.
