If, within 60 days of sending a statement for a consumer credit account, a creditor
receives a written notice from the borrower at the address provided for billing
inquiries (other than on a payment slip or another payment method, if the creditor
specified this requirement in the initial disclosure), from the obligor in which the
obligor:

