(b) Billing Error
For the purpose of this section, a "billing error" consists of any of the following:
(1) A charge on the statement for a credit transaction that the obligor did not make
or is shown for an incorrect amount.
(2) A charge on the statement for a credit transaction where the obligor requests
further clarification, including supporting documents.
(3) A charge on the statement for goods or services that the obligor or their
designee did not accept or did not receive as agreed upon in the transaction.
(4) The creditor's failure to accurately reflect a payment made by the obligor or a
credit issued to the obligor on the statement.
(5) A calculation or similar accounting error made by the creditor on the statement.
(6) Failure to send the required billing statement to the obligor's last known
address, provided the address was updated at least 20 days before the end of the
billing cycle for that statement.
(7) Any other error described in the regulations of the Bureau.
(c) Action by Creditor to Collect Amount or Any Part Thereof
Regarded by Obligor to Be a Billing Error
For the purposes of this section, "action to collect the amount, or any part thereof,
indicated by an obligor under paragraph (2)" does not include the sending of
statements of account, which may include finance charges on amounts in dispute,
to the obligor following written notice from the obligor as specified under
subsection (a), if:
(1) the obligor's account is not restricted or closed because of the failure of the
obligor to pay the amount indicated under paragraph (2) of subsection (a), and
(2) the creditor indicates the payment of such amount is not required pending the
