(d) Restricting or Closing by Creditor of Account Regarded by
Obligor to Contain a Billing Error
Under Bureau regulations, a creditor managing an open-end consumer credit plan
cannot restrict or close an account solely because the obligor has not paid an
amount they believe is a billing error, as long as the required written explanation or
clarification under paragraph (B)(ii) of subsection (a) has not yet been sent.
However, the creditor may still apply the disputed amount against the account’s
credit limit.
(e) Effect of Noncompliance with Requirements by Creditor
Any creditor who fails to comply with the requirements of this section or section
