by the obligor under paragraph (2) of subsection (a) of this section, and any finance
charges thereon, except that the amount required to be forfeited under this
subsection may not exceed $50.
Section 1666a: Regulation of Credit Reports
(a) Reports by Creditor on Obligor's Failure to Pay Amount
Regarded as Billing Error
After receiving a notice from an obligor, a creditor or their agent may not threaten
to report negatively on the obligor's credit rating or standing because the obligor
fails to pay the disputed amount. This amount cannot be reported as delinquent to
any third party until the creditor has fulfilled the requirements of section 1666 and

