Section 1666i: Assertion by Cardholder Against Card
Issuer of Claims and Defenses Arising Out of Credit
Card Transaction; Prerequisites; Limitation on
Amount of Claims or Defenses
(a) Claims and Defenses Assertible
Subject to the limitation contained in subsection (b), a card issuer who has issued a
credit card to a cardholder pursuant to an open-end consumer credit plan shall be
subject to all claims (other than tort claims) and defenses arising out of any
